1
00:00:14,801 --> 00:00:16,261
Dad, mom.

2
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:16,721
Slow down, baby.

3
00:00:16,721 --> 00:00:17,261
Wait.

4
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:23,241
Don't take this out.

5
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:24,821
You must come back safely.

6
00:00:25,101 --> 00:00:26,360
I will.

7
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:28,321
With your paper crane,

8
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:30,280
we'll be safe.

9
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,521
You spoil her too much.

10
00:00:33,101 --> 00:00:34,241
She's already grown up,

11
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:35,440
but still acts like a child.

12
00:00:35,460 --> 00:00:36,820
She's my baby.

13
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,021
You always laugh at me for not growing up,

14
00:00:50,580 --> 00:00:52,921
but I just want to be your daughter forever.

15
00:01:06,381 --> 00:01:07,601
You always say

16
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:11,841
the paper cranes I folded

17
00:01:12,421 --> 00:01:13,860
are the most efficacious.

18
00:01:16,661 --> 00:01:17,241
But

19
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,141
why

20
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:23,661
it couldn't bring you back safely?

21
00:02:10,161 --> 00:02:10,820
This

22
00:02:11,641 --> 00:02:12,941
is clearly a style

23
00:02:12,941 --> 00:02:14,141
that only I and my mom could fold.

24
00:02:14,721 --> 00:02:16,840
This is from when I was 19,

25
00:02:18,801 --> 00:02:21,441
[and twenty and twenty-one.]

26
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:24,781
[I put these paper cranes on the grave myself.]

27
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,920
[How come they are all here?]

28
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,341
[It has been five years.]

29
00:02:36,740 --> 00:02:38,681
[I don't know how many times I've visited the grave.]

30
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,881
[How did he do it?]

31
00:02:43,681 --> 00:02:47,441
How did you find these paper cranes?

32
00:02:50,601 --> 00:02:52,920
I've just been helping you

33
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,020
renew your faded and withered longing

34
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,961
over and over again.

35
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:05,341
How do you feel now?

36
00:03:06,621 --> 00:03:08,080
Why are you so good to me?

37
00:03:09,281 --> 00:03:10,121
Shouldn't you...

38
00:03:10,441 --> 00:03:11,640
I'm your husband.

39
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,300
Isn't it my duty to be nice to you?

40
00:03:15,661 --> 00:03:17,040
Everything you cherish

41
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,920
should be well kept.

42
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,061
Making you happy

43
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,800
is my top priority.

44
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:28,360
What are you up to?

45
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:30,601
To catch a prey,

46
00:03:30,601 --> 00:03:32,781
can you really disguise yourself to this extent?

47
00:04:13,101 --> 00:04:14,580
Everything goes according to the original plan.

48
00:04:16,161 --> 00:04:18,820
Your fake husband's real name is Zhou Xubai.

49
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:21,941
He graduated from Qing University two years before us.

50
00:04:21,941 --> 00:04:23,881
As for his family information, it's unknown.

51
00:04:23,881 --> 00:04:25,941
His motive is also unknown.

52
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:33,380
Zhou Xubai, Qing University.

53
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:35,620
He has been hiding by my side.

54
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:37,081
If so,

55
00:04:37,081 --> 00:04:38,940
it's not impossible to find out

56
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:40,641
the secret of the paper crane.

57
00:04:41,141 --> 00:04:42,620
He had already begun to plot

58
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:45,321
in college.

59
00:05:02,081 --> 00:05:05,081
Zhou Xubai, what should I do

60
00:05:05,581 --> 00:05:07,321
to tear off your disguise

61
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:08,901
[to make you hurt me?]

62
00:05:13,781 --> 00:05:14,281
Okay,

63
00:05:14,901 --> 00:05:16,040
you've had enough for today.

64
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:17,021
Don't drink too much.

65
00:05:19,401 --> 00:05:19,860
What?

66
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,540
Are you afraid I'll get drunk?

67
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,680
Then

68
00:05:25,101 --> 00:05:27,161
why don't you drink with me?

69
00:05:30,721 --> 00:05:31,281
Alright,

70
00:05:31,860 --> 00:05:32,821
let's go back and rest.

71
00:05:35,781 --> 00:05:36,800
Actually,

72
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,101
I know

73
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:40,540
you're not my husband.

74
00:05:43,281 --> 00:05:45,081
You've been lying to me.

75
00:05:51,601 --> 00:05:52,201
Zhimei,

76
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:54,081
you must be drunk.

77
00:05:54,101 --> 00:05:55,800
You're starting to talk nonsense.

78
00:06:22,341 --> 00:06:24,961
I'm more sober than ever.

79
00:06:33,221 --> 00:06:34,380
Why are you hiding?

80
00:06:35,101 --> 00:06:36,500
Am I not attractive,

81
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:38,601
or

82
00:06:39,980 --> 00:06:41,021
are you afraid of something?

83
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,401
You're really drunk.

84
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,021
Every time we touch,

85
00:07:00,341 --> 00:07:01,641
feels unfamiliar.

86
00:07:02,161 --> 00:07:03,201
Your heartbeat,

87
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,540
your scent,

88
00:07:06,401 --> 00:07:08,281
even the way you kiss me

89
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:10,601
is different from his.

90
00:07:14,721 --> 00:07:15,601
Different?

91
00:07:17,081 --> 00:07:19,021
Then let me show you

92
00:07:19,620 --> 00:07:21,000
who's holding you

93
00:07:21,461 --> 00:07:22,101
right now.

94
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:25,980
What are you doing?

95
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:05,060
Do you feel it now?

96
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:07,940
No.

97
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:22,761
I...

98
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,180
I'm going to the bathroom.

99
00:08:47,841 --> 00:08:48,520
Jiayi,

100
00:08:48,681 --> 00:08:50,020
I'm going to die.

101
00:08:51,061 --> 00:08:52,201
I saw everything.

102
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:54,681
Do you want him to kill you

103
00:08:55,041 --> 00:08:56,081
or kiss you to death?

104
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,520
Is this the time to tease?

105
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:00,640
How's it going on your side?

106
00:09:01,421 --> 00:09:02,301
All set.

107
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:04,041
Are you sure you want to continue?

108
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:06,081
Your heartbeat is almost

109
00:09:06,101 --> 00:09:07,280
can be heard through the phone.

110
00:09:09,801 --> 00:09:11,221
He can mess up my heartbeat,

111
00:09:12,601 --> 00:09:14,081
but he can't mess up my plan.

112
00:09:16,101 --> 00:09:16,520
Go on.

113
00:09:24,980 --> 00:09:26,041
Zhi Mei, watch out!

114
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:43,261
It's on fire!

115
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:44,381
What's going on?

116
00:09:50,820 --> 00:09:51,381
Hurry up!

117
00:09:51,381 --> 00:09:52,181
Run!

118
00:10:01,161 --> 00:10:02,801
It's on fire! Hurry up!

119
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:03,700
Go!

120
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:07,641
Go!

121
00:10:28,181 --> 00:10:29,200
Mei Mei.

122
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:29,681
What's going on?

123
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,541
Hurry up.

124
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:31,340
Run!

125
00:10:33,141 --> 00:10:33,921
Hurry.

126
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:34,860
Wait,

127
00:10:35,161 --> 00:10:36,360
you're not softening up, are you?

128
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:56,320
Let's go.

129
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,681
If we wait any longer, it'll be too late.

130
00:11:01,580 --> 00:11:02,840
Zhi Mei.

131
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,480
Zhi Mei.

132
00:11:09,801 --> 00:11:10,960
Zhi Mei.

133
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,761
Zhimei.

134
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:21,580
Zhou Xubai.

135
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:25,340
Zhou Xubai.

136
00:11:26,681 --> 00:11:27,881
Zhou Xubai.

137
00:11:52,781 --> 00:11:53,681
I'm glad you're okay.

138
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,301
[You took the bullet for me.]

139
00:12:17,641 --> 00:12:19,881
[But why did you]

140
00:12:20,181 --> 00:12:22,401
[give me a fake name?]
